Saturday August 31st 2013 10:38 am -04:00,The difference is that when you write >>> yesnoyesnoYoure getting the representation of the string literal that means the exact characters that are contained in it. So the interpreter is not converting the escaped characters (the newline  character) into an actual new line. If you do this>>> print(yesno)yesnoThen youre getting the output from the print() function which converts all escaped characters.Hope this helps!, Unresolved,4
